item.title: India use spin, death-bowling strengths to restrict Australia
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Australia lost their way after a strong start, succumbing to India's spin strength through the middle phase of their innings. Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav and Kedar Jadhav bowled 30 overs between them for 136 runs and four wickets as Australia managed only 242 for 9 after electing to bat first in Nagpur.
The relaid wicket at the VCA Stadium didn't quite live up to the curator's assessment of it being a 300-run surface. But Steven Smith didn't have any qualms in taking first strike despite a brief spell of showers in the build up to the game. The new ball presented the batting side with the best period to score against and in keeping with their recent form, Aaron Finch and David Warner quickly set about building a sturdy platform for Australia.
Jasprit Bumrah, reinstated in the playing XI along with Bhuvneshwar Kumar and Kuldeep, began with a maiden. But his next three overs cost India 34 with Australia's openers cashing in on a curious short-ball strategy that failed in its execution. By the eight-over mark, Finch had five boundaries and Warner had three as Australia scored at exactly a run-a-ball. Finch was first to go, having registered his third 50-plus stand with Warner, attempting to hit Hardik Pandya over the top but only succeeding in toe-ending to mid-off.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!
